:R-HSA-112311  a            obo:GO_0008150 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "Neurotransmitter released in the synaptic cleft binds to specific receptors on the post-synaptic cell and the excess of the neurotransmitter is cleared to prevent over activation of the post-synaptic cell. The neurotransmitter is cleared by either re-uptake by the pre-synaptic neuron, diffusion in the perisynaptic area, uptake by astrocytes surrounding the synaptic cleft or enzymatic degradation of the neurotransmitter." ;
        rdfs:label          "Neurotransmitter clearance" ;
        dc:contributor      "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Edited: Mahajan, SS, 2008-01-14 16:01:52" , "Authored: Mahajan, SS, 2008-01-14 16:01:52" , "Reviewed: Restituito, S, 2008-11-27 12:38:49" ;
